inn1.comm: switches to an outside off line, length delivery, Strauss looks to drive that one through the off, gets an inside edge on to his pads
doesn't take too long for Brett Lee to bring out the bouncer, Strauss ducks under that one
length ball on off, defended towards the bowler, a hint of movement away for Lee
short of length ball, on leg stump and sliding down, off the thigh pad behind square leg
short and wide from Lee, first chance for Strauss to free his arms, he guides that one down to third man, and England are away, Lee working up some good pace in that over
he begins with a length ball on offstump, punched towards mid-off

short of length ball, just outside off, Strauss pulls it past a diving midwicket, timing wasn't great so the ball doesn't go all the way, but there's a long, long chase for the fielder, and England scamper four runs anyway
just outside off, Strauss looks to swat that towards midwicket again, he misses
similar delivery from Bollinger, Strauss stands tall and defends this one
on offstump, again it is not too short but Strauss goes for the pull, not off the middle of the bat, squirts away towards square leg
attempted yorker, ends up as a very full toss on middle and off, dug past midwicket

two chances for a dismissal, an attempted pull lands wide of the keeper after which Australia make a mess of a run-out, it was a quick bouncer from Lee, loops of the glove, Davies wanted the single and charged out, Strauss didn't want one, so Davies has to rush back, there seemed to be plenty of time to run out Davies without facing a ball, instead the throw from Bollinger is wide of the crease, Lee was hustling back towards the stumps and Smith was backing up, Smith collects and underarms the ball from a couple of yards away and misses the stumps, he was blinded the bowler coming back towards the stumps, Davies is a relieved man
pushed off the backfoot towards square leg for a single
first ball for Davies, defended to the off side
length ball on off, pushed towards cover by Davies
Davies gets his first run by steering the ball towards a wide third man
pitched up and just outside off from Lee, Strauss punches it with superb timing between the bowler and mid-off for a boundary
back of a length ball outside off, defended towards point
slightly overpitched, on the pads, whipped towards midwicket by Davies
just short of a length from Bollinger, Strauss punches it off the front foot towards the off side
it's a quick bouncer from Bollinger, Strauss has already shown he's keen on the pull and hook, he attempts to smash this to the leg side, but he doesn't connect, it's deemed a wide, tight call that
into middle and leg, Strauss works the ball towards midwicket, quickly calls 'No' to let Davies know he doesn't want a single
in the channel outside off, Strauss looking to help that towards square leg, gets a thick inside-edge onto his pads, and the ball dribbles towards point
strays onto leg, Strauss tucks that in front of square leg for a single to retain the strike
the pull hasn't exactly been working for Strauss today, but he keeps attempting it to deliveries outside off, another inside-edge, on to the body this time
Lee keeps it on a shortish length, on legstump this time, Strauss tries to help it along towards fine leg, bottom-edge to short fine leg

and Strauss continues to live on the edge, a slower bouncer from Lee outside off, Strauss brings out the pull again, gets a top-edge this time, and there's plenty of excited calls of 'catch' from the Australian fielders but the ball loops over short fine
Lee finally pitches one up, punched off the front foot towards extra cover

the pull shot has finally led to a wicket, oh hang on, it's a no-ball, Davies pulls another short one from Lee, doesn't get hold of it, easy catch to fine leg, Australia are celberating, Davies is on his way, umpire says 'wait a minute, I want to see whether Lee has overstepped', replays show that Lee has indeed crossed the line, so Davies survives, first time that rule has been used in one-dayers
Lee serves up a half-tracker, Strauss responds to the gift with an awkward swat, connects well enough though and sends the ball racing past mid-off for four
fires in a full delivery, line is wrong this time, down the leg side and another free run for England
switches back to the short length, Strauss defends off the back foot towards the off side
Bollinger also keeps it short, batsman pulls, with better placement this time and it gets him a couple to deep midwicket
worked towards square leg off the back foot for a single
full and on the pads, whipped away towards fine leg for a couple
length ball on middle and leg, gets his front leg out of the way and slaps that past mid-on for a boundary, runs starting to flow now for England
Bolinger serves it up on a length, just outside off, Davies opens the face to guide that one past the keeper and fine of third man for a boundary, wasn't totally in control of that one
'Catch' is the call again as Davies flatbats the ball towards mid-on, lands well short of the fielder
more short-pitched stuff, more pulls, a single results after the ball is sent to deep square leg
short of length and down the leg side, Davies looks to pull that one, gets it off the glove towards the keeper, who dives to the right to collect the ball after it bounces on its way to him
length ball, pushed off the front foot towards mid-off

dropped by Shane Watson, it was a very tough chance, a short of length ball outside off is hammered by Davies towards short cover, it's low and to the left of Watson, who has very little time to react, he sticks his hand out, it's in his palm for an instant but it doesn't stick
Lee keeps it short, Davies goes for the pull, mistimes it to the leg side

Davies goes for the hook to another short one down the leg side, he doesn't get hold of it, Haddin appeals for a caught-behind, umpire says no and calls it a wide, good thing for Australia that they didn't call for the review as Lee has overstepped
quick bouncer on offstump line, defended off the back foot towards the bowler
first ball is cracked towards cover point, Brett Lee moves quickly to cut that off
whipped towards squre leg by Strauss for a single
worked to sweeper cover for a couple by Davies
wonderful shot to bring up the fifty, a length ball just outside off, Davies responds with a lofted inside-out drive over extra cover, ball speeds away for a boundary

not as good from Davies this time, and Haddin misses a stumping, Davies was looking for another big hit, coming down the track and aiming for the long-on boundary, he misses the ball which stays low, sneaks past legstump, Haddin doesn't collect and Davies' charmed life continues
short ball from Hussey, clipped towards square leg for a single
square leg and midwicket continue to be profitable for Strauss, short of length ball is slapped towards deep square for a single
outside off from Johnson, Davies guides it down to third man for a single
this time it is Strauss who pokes a ball outside off towards third man for another single
outside off and left alone by Davies

shortish from Johnson outside off, another mess of a pull from Davies, takes the top-edge and could have gone anywhere, it almost goes all the way for six near third man, lands wide of the fielder and runs away for four, Davies is a lucky, lucky man today
fires one down the leg side
works the ball down to third man for a single
short of length ball outside off, pushed it to point
length ball angling across, Davies just stands in his crease and launches it over extra cover for  a boundary, makes it look very easy, supremely timing from Davies
keeps it on a length, punched by Davies towards mid-off
makes a bit of room and carves that one over deep backward point for a couple
length ball on off, Davies moves across his stumps and tucks the ball towards midwicket
a touch shorter, and just outside off, pushed back towards the bowler
full on off stump, Davies stays on the crease and guides it to point for one

ooh, shot from Strauss, who can hammer these short balls all day and night. Johnson lands it in the halfway house and it nips away a bit, but why is that going to worry Strauss? He gets back and across, and creams it away through point
over-compensates with a full delivery on the toes which Strauss glances with the angle towards fine leg
slower ball of sorts, 127 kph, back of a length outside off and Davies drops it with soft hands for another single
tripe from Mitch. Another one sliding down the leg side and Strauss gladly gets inside the line and tickles it along the way to fine leg
shifts to the line outside off, a touch too full at 140 kph and Strauss drives powerfully, bvut straight to mid off
back of a length outside off and Davies seemed to be lining him up for the carve before deciding to steer it square for one

this is a violent start from Strauss. He's been bashing the short stuff all-round. He hasn't got a short ball for a couple of deliveries, so he charges out, keeping the off side open, gets to the length and tees away over mid-off
fuller on off stump and he drives to mid off for a single
short ball and Davies was beside himself with eagerness to pull, and ended up mistiming the shot for a single
in the slot for the drive, Strauss drives through the covers for another single
Watto holds the length back a touch, Davies stays in the crease and guides behind point with an angled face. England chug along.

and that's exactly what Hussey has produced. Davies' lottery run comes to an end. Hussey's speared this in off a round-arm, flat from wide of the crease, round the wicket, and it straightens past an attempted mow through cow corner and clattered into the furniture. Australia will breathe easier now.
back of a length outside off, turning into Trott who nudges to the leg side off the back foot
Haddin lets out a huge appeal for lbw, unsupported by D Hussey. It was a skidder that held its line as Strauss played back and it seemed like it hit bat before pad. In fact it did not hit pad at all.
ooh, the reverse sweep, Strauss changes the grip and slaps well, but straight to short third man
tossed up further on middle and leg, Strauss presses forward and works it to midwicket
Watson grunts as he delivers that short of length ball outside off, Strauss gets on the back foot and pulls the ball towards midwicket
short of length ball outside off, Strauss makes a touch of room, guides the ball down towards third man
similar length from Watson and just outside off, Trott jumps across the stumps and looks to work that one towards fine leg, gets an edge which takes it very fine past the keeper for four
solidly defended off the front foot by Trott
keeps it accurate around offstump, Trott gets behind the line and defends towards cover

pushed towards mid-on, Trott zips through for a single, for a moment it looked like it might be tight but he comfortably beats the throw from the fielder who had to run in a bit before getting to the ball
short ball on off, Trott goes for the reverse-sweep but he doesn't connect because of the extra bounce, into his body

a smart catch from Haddin ends Trott's innings, a short of length ball pitches outside off and turns in gently, Trott is on the back foot quickly and looks to guide it towards third man, gets an outside edge and Haddin snaps it up, Hussey helping Australia pull things back, not doing his World Cup chances any harm here
full ball outside off, defended off the front foot
more defence from KP, this time to the leg side

again there are shouts of 'catch' but that was hit hard into the ground, a full toss outside off, Pietersen thumps it towards cover, where the fielder can't latch on the ball at shoulder-height to his left, allows a single
worked towards midwicket for a single
stats with a full ball outside off, swept by Strauss towards square leg
full toss outside off, punched to long-off
way outside off, Strauss looks to steer it to third man but misses

a howler from Haddin, he misses the second stumping of the day, Strauss was yards out of the crease and missed the wide delivery from Doherty, Haddin had a simple chance to get rid of the England captain, but he doesn't collect the ball
punched to long-on for a single
on a length outside off, defended off the front foot
width from Hussey, Pietersen stretches across and crashes the ball through covers for his first boundary
Pietersen gets well forward to convert that delivery into a yorker, dug out towards point
looks to flick this one towards midwicket, gets an outside edge which takes the ball towards short third
Strauss bring up the fifty by punching the ball off the front foot past extra cover
Hussey keeps it full, Strauss nurdles the ball in front of square leg
'Two,' called Strauss after flat-batting a short ball towards long-on off the back foot, Pietersen races the first but decides against the second
guides this one down to fine leg for a couple
length ball outside off, Pietersen is down the track looking to defend, struck on the pads but outside off, muted appeal from Australia
a wristy on-drive to long-on gets KP a single
looks to sweep a full ball from outside off, he misses, Haddin collects and breaks the stumps, but Strauss' backfoot was planted in the crease all along
gets this one away to sqaure leg for a single
pushed towards extra cover for a single
Pietersen is looking to come down the track on most deliveries to the spinners, eases it down to long-on
pushes this one towards mid-on
Strauss comes out of the crease and drags a full ball from outside off past mid-on for a boundary
dabs this one from the crease towards cover
on the pads, tucked in front of square leg by Strauss
paddle-sweeps from outside off towards short fine leg
another full ball well outside off, Pietersen decides to sweep that one but misses
length ball heading for off, defended solidly off the front foot
Pietersen takes a couple of paces down the track and drives the ball along the ground to long-on for an easy single
on a length and on off, steady from Doherty, tucked behind square leg
again Pietersen charges out of the crease, this time he defends towards cover
immediately he sends down a short ball, Strauss respond with the pull, picks up a single to deep midwicket
a low full toss outside off, jabbed past the bowler for a single, Strauss was late to respond, but there are no alarms as the batsmen complete the run easily
another low full toss, driven towards mid-off by Strauss

that's the end of Strauss, Lee strikes, a short of length ball around middle, Strauss was initially looking to pull that to square leg, then decides to play with a straight bat, the ball loops off the bat towards midwicket where Clarke is waiting
quick length ball outside off, Bell is drawn towards the one, he's beaten as he looks to drive, Lee follows-through and gives Bell a glare
short of length ball outside off, Bell gets on the back foot and helps the ball towards third man
Pietersen sweeps a full ball behind square leg
length ball outside off, pushed towards cover by Bell
flighted delivery from Doherty, around off, defended by Bell towards the bowler
full, on middle and leg, pushed towards mid-on by Bell
Steven Smith races across from short cover to field a punch from Bell
driven off the backfoot past the bowler for a single that ends a quiet over
Lee starts this over with a length ball, defended solidly by Bell
slightly shorter from Lee, but tight line around off, blocked off the back foot towards point
overpitched and a bit wide from Lee, driven off the front foot past cover
Pietersen moves across the stumps early, a short of length ball outside off, Pietersen looks to defend towards cover, gets an inside-edge towards midwicket, a quick single is taken
short and a bit of width on offer for Bell, who plays a very controlled late cut, down to third man, nicely done by Bell
attempts the bouncer, sits up for Pietersen well outside off, he tries to swat that powerfully to midwicket, bottom-edges onto his boot
wonderful stroke from Bell, overpitched and on the pads from Doherty, Bell chips it over midwicket, very well timed to get a boundary
outside off, chopped towards gully
on middle and leg, played with soft hands towards midwicket, Bell calls early for the single
length ball on middle and off, Pietersen reverts to his usual tactic of walking down the track, drives the ball down to long-on
another single, delicately played in front of square leg
nothing delicate in that stroke, Pietersen's out of his crease and looks to hammer a wide ball through cover, picks up a single
short of length ball and way down the leg side, poor from Bollinger

similiar length and closer to legstump, Pietersen works it behind square after taking a couple of paces down the track, and screams 'push, push', a good throw from the deep would have had him in trouble, but it was wide from Doherty
looks for a powerful pull, but doesn't quite get hold of it, mistimed towards deep midwicket
guided down to fine leg where Doherty fields
short of length ball just outside off, dropped to the off side and a single is taken
way outside off, just close enough to the stumps to satisfy the umpire that it was a legit delivery, Pietersen gives the umpire a glare
much-better delivery to end the over, short of length and on middle and off, Bell gets on the back foot and blocks that one
whipped off the pads towards midwicket
sliding onto the pads again, worked in front of square leg for another single
a paddle-sweep from way outside off, it was a bottom-edge form KP, sends the ball fine past the keeper
solidly defended off the front foot by Pietersen
opens the face to guide the ball towards short third man for a single
Doherty grunts as he delivers that one, outside off and dabbed to short third, went too quickly to get a single
short of length ball is played off the front foot towards cover by Pietersen
short of length, opens the face and plays the ball towards short third
shortish ball, slapped past a diving White at point, White got a hand to that one but couldn't stop it
short ball, not very well timed pull from Bell, the ball drops towards midwicket
length ball heading for off, punched down the ground for a single
short of length ball and outside off, guided down to third man for a single
loads of width for Bell to work with, he dabs the ball down to third man
Pietersen continues to advance down the track, drilled down to long-on for a single
Bell continues to pick up runs down to third man, easily done
Pietersen plants his front well forward to a short of length legcutter, beaten by the bounce
fuller from Watson, this time Pietersen connects nicely this time, to long-off
third single to third man in the over for Bell, no frills for him
almost gets a wicket first ball, Bell looks to paddle sweep that, top edge onto the body and luckily for him it doesn't pop up to Haddin, lands in front of the batsman
pushed towards extra cover for a single
another pre-meditated sweep, he misses
flicked stylishly towards midwicket
full and way outside off, Bell reaches across and then sweeps towards square leg
a wristy shot towards the leg side, no run
cuts in after pitching on a length outside off, defended by Bell to the off side, takes a brisk single
length ball from Watson, punched firmly back towards the bowler
Pietersen walks down the track and hammers the slower ball back towards the bowler, on the bounce to Watson who tries to field that but is hit on the wrist
quicker ball, short of length outside off, beaten as he looks to jab it towards cover, there's a noise but it's KP's bat hitting his pad
punched towards long-on, where Steven Smith misfields, no extra run given away
chopped towards point for a single to end the over

soft dismissal that, Smith has struck, a length ball, Bell was looking to chip it inside-out over extra cover, he doesn't get the height he wanted, ends up hitting it towards Clarke at extra cover, a threatening partnership has been broken
length ball outside off, driven towards point by Morgan
defended by Morgan off the front foot
down the leg side, helped fine by Morgan, Watson chases and makes a sliding stop but his foot touches the rope
flighted delivery, driven to the off side
fuller from Smith, driven firmly back to the bowler, who fields and fires the ball back to the keeper
length ball just outside off, worked wristily down to long-on for an ambled single
length ball on off, defended off the front foot
slightly shorter, on middle and leg, Morgan comes down the track and pushes the ball towards midwicket
just a bit of width from Watson, Morgan rocks back and cracks that to point, doesn't beat the fielder
length ball outside off, worked towards sweeper cover by Morgan for a single
lovely drive all along the ground to long-on, came down the track and stood tall as he played that
full and on the pads, again KP uses his feet and drives the ball to long-on
full and wide, Morgan stretches and drives the ball towards sweeper cover
full toss and very wide, Morgan whips the ball down to long-off
Pietersen sweeps a full ball on off behind square leg for another single

Smith has another, a short of length ball, Morgan played that off the back foot after making room, he jabs it hard but in the air and towards White at short cover, White dives to his right to snap that up, that's another wicket and Australia are the team with the edge now, England have frittered that powerful start, Pietersen needs to play a big innings now
Yardy aims an extravagant drive off his first delivery, it was a full ball outside off and Yardy can't connect
Haddin's horror day continues, another stumping chance, Pietersen was down the track and missed a wide, full ball from Hussey, into Haddin's gloves and out, that would have been a massive wicket
driven to long-on for a single
looks for the paddle-sweep, top edge from Yardy, flies over the keeper for a single
that was a hit-me full toss from Hussey, Pietersen dances down the track and clobbers that over long-on for six
and another monster hit to reach his fifty, again he charges out and muscles a flat six over long-on, this one travels a long way into the stands, a great way to end his one-day drought
this time Pietersen drives along the ground to long-on
terrible delivery from Johnson, short and miles down the leg side, would have been a wide to a left-hander, the crowd has a big laugh
another one down the leg side, Pietersen aims a powerful pull but misses
much better from Johnson, short of length and outside off, dropped towards cover by Pietersen for a single
length ball heading for off, Yardy gets behind the line and defends
short and outside off, Yardy wafts at it as he looks to guide to third man, misses
pitched up from Johnson, front-foot defense from Yardy
this time Yardy gets the ball down to third man for a single
length ball outside off, jabbed towards point by Pietersen for a single
Pietersen survives as he nicks a back of length ball outside off, flies through the vacant slip area for four
similar length and on off stump, played towards cover and sets off for a tight single, makes it in time
fuller ball from Bollinger, defended by Yardy to the off side
length delivery heading for off, Yardy had shuffled across his stumps early on, he pushes the ball towards cover
full and slanting into the pads, tucked towards deep midwicket, Yardy wanted the second but Pietersen sent him back
back of length ball, inside-edged onto the pads by Pietersen
Johnson starts with another regulation leg-side wide
length ball on middle and off, tucked towards square leg

Johnson gets it right finally, very right, a bouncer surprises Pietersen, he was going for the hook but the ball gets big on him, turns away from the ball and crashes into the side of helmet, the ball loops high towards the keeper, Pietersen doesn't know quite where it is, so he stands over the stumps to ensure the ball doesn't ball on it, smart work from KP
full and wide, slapped to sweeper cover for a single
Yardy gets behind the line and defends to the off side
back of length ball outside off, guided towards third man for a single
length ball on off, pushed towards cover for a single to end the over
short of length ball outside off, Pietersen makes a bit of room to look to guide the ball towards third man, the ball sails over the top edge of his bat
Pietersen was shuffling across the stumps early, Bollinger sees that and fires a yorker which is just outside leg, gets called for a wide
another yorker from Bollinger, but well outside off, off the inside-edge towards midwicket
length ball on off, dropped towards point
another length delivery, Yardy drives that off the front foot to cover
short ball outside off from Bollinger, Yardy goes for the pull, badly mistimed, the ball is in the air for a bit but lands wide of short cover
shorter this time and on offstump, defended by Yardy to the leg side
fired into the legstump, driven down to long-on for a single

Yardy attempts the reverse-sweep, that ball was oh-so-close to the offstump, Yardy gets a thin egde, the ball misses off, Haddin misses the ball, Bollinger has to chase to pull that in just inside the rope
Yardy goes for the regulation sweep, in the air and lands behinds square leg
great running from KP, gets two though that ball was hit just beyond the inner circle, it was a legstump delivery, tucked towards square leg
lovely from KP, charges down the track to get to the pitch of the ball and hammers it flat over the bowler's head for six, powerful hit!
an elegant extra cover drive to end the over
a bouncer from Bollinger, way over Pietersen's head, Haddin jumps and tries to collect with one outstretched hand, gets glove on it but can't prevent the bye
another short one, Yardy mistimes another pull, lands short of mid-on
back of length and outside off, dabbed towards third man for a single
a knee-high full toss outside off, KP mistimes a drive to mid-off
finally Yardy perishes to the pull, he has mishit several of them today, this time he gets hold of it and it carries only as far as Michael Hussey at deep midwicket
short of length ball on middle and leg, Pietersen hit on the thigh pad as he looks to defend
similar length from Bolinger, on middle, Pietersen punches it back towards the bowler
a swish-and-miss from Bresnan to a ball outside off
short of length ball outside off, mistimes a pull towards midwicket
a bit of width, Bresnan goes after it hard, gets a n edge that flies past the keeper to the third man boundary
another attempted powerful hit from Bresnan, he looks to crash the ball past extra cover, no contact
short ball from Hussey, Bresnan goes for the pull, connects well finally, Michael Hussey has work to do in the deep
pitchd up and just outside off, driven towards mid-off by Bresnan
short of length outside off, KP hits it towards cover
short of length ball on middle and off, defended to the off side
similar length on the legstump, 'catch' is the cry but the only man who could have is the square-leg umpire
shortish ball just outside off, makes a bit of room and slaps that down to third man
back of a length ball around off, Bresnan makes room and gets an outside edge towards third man
good-looking shot, but not very well timed, all along the ground past the bowler
driven down to long-on for a single to bring up the 250 for England
defended back towards the bowler by Bresnan
length ball on middle and leg, tucked towards midwicket
Pietersen walks across the stumps and drives a length ball towards sweeper cover
Bresnan backs away and chops the ball towards point
length ball is pushed back towards the bowler
full and wide, cracked towards cover
length ball just outside off, smoked down the ground for four
length ball outside off, Bresnan mistimes a cover drive

superb work from Johnson, Pietersen's run-out, massive blow for England, Johnson might be having a tough time with the ball, but don't question his footballing skills, he bangs in a short ball, Bresnan looks to pull it, he misses and the ball hits him on the chest and rolls to the leg side, KP is very keen on a single and calls Bresnan though, Johnson races towards the ball and right-foots it onto the stumps, catching Pietersen well short
length ball outside off, Swann slices that towards backward point
slower ball from Johnson, short and wide but Swann can't connect
short and wide slower ball from Lee to start, Bresnan cuts that hard to Smith at cover, Swann sets off for a single, David Hussey dives to do the backing  up after the throw from Smith misses
shortish ball outside leg, batsman was backing away early, helped towards midwicket for a single
slower bouncer from Lee, Bresnan doesn't pick it up, he was early into his attempted hook, adjusts late and gets it off the toe-end towards fine leg, gets enough on it to get a boundary
pushed just wide of Brett Lee to get a single
Swann goes for an ambitious swipe to a short of length ball just outside off, he misses and the ball zips through to the keeper
Johnson starts the over with a full and wide delivery,  Bresnan looks to crash that through cover, but doesn't make contact
crowd are excited as Bresnan thumps a short ball back towards the bowler, mistimed and Johnson does well to field
Bresnan swipes this one down the ground, Swann pushes him to come back for the second
Johnson gets the line totally wrong, outside leg and Bresnan clips that nicely behind square, well timed that
fullish ball outside off, muscled towards sweeper cover
bouncer down the leg side, batsman had backed away a long way, he tries to jab that past the keeper to third man but can't get bat on it
powered to extra cover, that was overpitched outside off, can't get it past the fielder

short and outside off, Bresnan looks to slash that one, gets a top-edge which sails to Doherty at third man, Lee is thrilled as he thought he had Davies caught at third man earlier before replays showed he had overstepped, no such worries this time
full and well outside off, sliced down to third man
short ball outside off, Shahzad jumps as the ball rises but doesn't offer a shot, that was a quick delivery
this was the slower bouncer, Shahzad mistimes the pull, the ball lands short of deep midwicket
fired down the leg side by Lee, batsman looks to tickle it to fine leg but misses
came down the track and blocked it back to the bowler
full and just outside off, jabbed past backward point by Swann, one run short says the umpire so England get only a single
length ball again well outside off, Swann drags it towards mid-on
Shahzad backs away, Johnson follows him and the batsman is struck on the pad and the ball rolls towards square leg
slower ball angling away, Swann can't connect

and another catch for Doherty, can England play out the 50 overs? there have inly one wicket left now as Swann holes out, a slower ball from Johnson, Swann looks to clear the in-field but can't chip it past Doherty at mid-on
on middle and leg, batsman gets behind the line and defends
Lee nearly finishes the innings with a pinpoint yorker, Tremlett does well to keep that out

the review system is being used for the first time in ODIs, Australia have asked for it after Shahzad is struck on the back pad outside leg and goes through to the keeper, Lee think there's an inside-edge and asks for a caught-behind, replays don't show a nick, there were two noises as the ball flicked the front pad before thudding into the back pad, Tremlett survives
another yorker, outside off, Tremlett can't get bat on it
Lee keeps chruning out the yorker,best delivery to the tailender, this one was heading for middle and off, Tremlett defends
this was short from Lee, Tremlett ducks, he is called through for a bye, the batsmen scramble one, Lee lucky that wasn't called a wide since the bouncer was down leg
whoah! Lee attempts a yorker again, just gets is wrong, Shahzad gets under that one and launches over mid-off, plenty of power behind that shot and that goes on for a six
length ball heading for middle, Tremlett makes room and slaps it towards mid-on
short ball on legstump, swung down to Watson at fine leg
another biggie, this time from Tremlett, a massive six, shortish ball outside leg, Tremlett made room and swiped that with incredible power, sends the ball soaring over midwicket
another of those crazy Johnson deliveries, miles down the leg side
the end of the innings, Tremlett had cleared the front leg to attempt another monster hit, it was a short of length ball from Johnson, takes the top edge and goes through at a nice height to Haddin

inn2.comm: nice and straight to start, good length too. Coming in gently off the seam, and Watson steps forward to defend to mid-on
Watson is away! Too straight from Bresnan, slipping towards leg stump and Watson just had to get a touch on it - fine leg is very square
full again, but outside off this time and Watson aims a crunchy drive right at mid-off
cracked square on the drive this time, Morgan fields nicely on the bounce
delicate late cut from Watson, but Yardy's fielding down at third man is just as good and saves two runs
shaping gently away through the air, Watson steps well forward and drives into the covers
full and shaping away to start - this was quite wide and went even further. A thick outside edge bounces down to third man
slap! Wide again, and short this time. Watson cashes in with a flashing cut that beats a diving point and also evades third man
that's better from Tremlett, he straightens his line and Watson stays deep in the crease to defend back down the track
Watto is looking to impose himself early here, lunging forward to drive hard into the covers. He finds the fielder, however
great length from Tremlett, drawing the batsman forward but extracting enough bounce to hit the splice as Watson defends to extra cover
slightly wider of off, Watson steps forward and runs it off the face of the blade down to third man
flung down on a length, but outside off and easily left alone. Not a great deal of movement on offer for the quicks so far
cracking drive! Watson is great to watch when he's in this sort of form, he strides confidently down the pitch and slams a technically perfect drive through the covers. Power and placement.
clipped down to third man, they push hard and that's well run for two
Bresnan adjusts his line, attacking the stumps, and Watson defends
Watson's just tried to make too much of this, it was short and wide and there to be hit but he tried to smash it too hard and ends up hitting it hard into the ground and straight to point
a thick inside edge thumps into the pad and rolls to leg, and Watson will keep the strike as they scamper through for one
a handsome straight drive! Tremlett goes full and Watson is parked on the front foot waiting for the ball, the left elbow leads the shot and mid-on has no chance
Tremlett pulls the length back, Watson defends to cover with a hop
properly short this time from the bowler, Watson rocks back and pulls out into the deep - but there's a man out there, Pietersen, to stop the boundary
Haddin faces up to just his second ball, nudging a full delivery just wide of mid-on for a quick single
Watson drops a back-of-a-length delivery close in on the off side and briefly considers a cheeky single, but the fielder is in too quickly
nicely done, not a great deal of width to work with as the ball lands on a length on off stump, but Watson just stays on leg stump and glides it down to third man for one
tight, length delivery right on middle and off. Watson defends

Watson is in top form here, hitting the ball just where he wants to. The slip fielder had just been moved - Strauss it was - and so Watson aims a delicate late cut right through that region, beating Pietersen at third man for a boundary
hmm, and he follows that up with a much more awkward-looking chop down to that third man fielder. Still, gets the job done and that's a single

well, the batsman steps away to leg and swings mightily at a length delivery outside off - hitting only fresh air. It was the cross-seamed delivery from Bresnan, and it gripped a touch on the wicket and moved away from the bat
slower ball this time, but picked by Haddin who nudges into the leg side for one
Bresnan hones in on a good length, Watson defends
Tremlett charges in and seems to put a bit more effort into this one, finding significant lift off the wicket as Haddin hangs back and defends to point
and Haddin picks out gully exactly, chopping it straight to Strauss on the bounce
nice little shot from Haddin, as Tremlett slips too full and too straight and is worked out to deep midwicket
Tremlett lets one go with a grunt and finds a good length on off stump. Played down to gully. He's looking for third man with the shot
slower ball from Tremlett, Watson was early stepping forward but re-adjusted quickly and cracked the full delivery to point
short, pulled hard out towards wide midwicket but Pietersen charges across and tumbles over to save the boundary. Great fielding. Good field placement for Watson too
good start, hitting a length and moving in to the right-hander, who steps back and defends
Haddin gives himself some room but Shahzad's rhythm isn't disturbed and he aims a length ball at the off stump. Tapped to cover
dropped down close on the off side, there's no run to be had as the fielder swoops
back of a length from Shahzad, he keeps Haddin deep in the crease as the ball is defended towards mid-on
short and wider of off stump this time, Haddin doesn't take full toll, just pushing it down to third man
Shahzad attacks middle and off on a good length, Watson defends watchfully to mid-on
Haddin looks decidedly nervy out there, again he steps away to leg and tries to slash up and over the off side field ... but is beaten on the outside edge by a touch of extra bounce
lucky! Haddin backs away and aims an uncertain poke at a back-of-a-length delivery, a thick inside edge rolls wide of fine leg and that's four. Wasn't too far away from the stumps though
for the third time Haddin steps to leg, this time drilling it hard to mid-off
back of a length, the ball comes off Haddin's hip and they nip through for a leg bye
worked off the pad, behind square on the leg side and they're back for the second
just short of a good length, Watson steps back and pulls out into the deep but Pietersen is there to cut the shot off
good slower ball from Shahzad, but Watson spots it and defends
just outside off this time, again it's slower through the air, tapped to point. That was the legcutter, he just ran the fingers over the ball and got it to grip a touch
fuller and quicker, Watson aims a cautious drive straight to mid-on
curving in through the air, but the ball starts too wide of off and Watson is able to punch out to deep point for a couple
slower again, much slower this time. For a moment it appeared as though Watson was going to have a heave at this, but he just held himself back and opted for defence instead
this time he does have a go, and slams it in some style into the crowd behind long-on! It was another slower ball from Shahzad, but too full. That was a 101-metre six, quite a monster
cramping the batsman for room, the ball is tapped into the leg side

a top-edged pull, the ball swirls up, hanging in the air for an age ... and it's dropped by Trott, running back from mid-on! It was a really tough chance, he leapt back trying to take it over his shoulder but just got a hand to it and couldn't hold on
chopped down to gully
swatted out into the deep on the leg side, an aggressive front-foot pull from the batsman
just short of a good length, Haddin steps across to off and nudges to midwicket for a quick single
whipped off the front pad and out into the leg side, and that's the first Powerplay done
pushed to mid-off
Yardy, coming round the wicket, fires one in at leg stump and is clipped to midwicket. Shahzad sprints across and does really well to prevent the second run
looped up much slower, full on leg stump, and Haddin drives down to long-on
nudged just wide of midwicket, and that's fifty for Shane Watson. His team really need him to stick around and play through the innings
flicked out to deep square leg for one
and worked out into the leg side once more
punched down to long-on for one
a hint of turn for Swann, but it's slow turn and easily negotiated by Haddin, tapped into the leg side
tossed up on a perfect length outside off, Watson steps forward and defends with bat and pad right together
just a bit too short from Swann, Watson rocks back and pulls hard out to deep midwicket
floated down outside off, Watson gets back and across and defends to cover
slightly too wide of off, Watson glides one just wide of short third man and they scamper through
speared at leg stump, flicked to short fine leg
held back a touch, the ball grips and spins slowly away. Watson stays deep in the crease and punches hard to mid-off. They sprint through for one
eased down to long-on
singles on offer here, Watson pushing down to long-off
much slower through the air, Haddin defends
driven out to deep cover, he sliced at it a touch but played along the ground and in the gap
Haddin begins with a boundary! Stepping away to leg to a length delivery, he uses the resultant width to crack a cut shot out to the boundary
fuller and straighter from Bresnan, Haddin taps slightly awkwardly to midwicket
again Haddin gives himself room, forcing off the back foot but straight to the point fielder this time
slower ball from Bresnan, giving Haddin no width to work with and he's quietly defended to mid-on
sharp running! That was pretty close, nudged to gully and they just set off despite the fielder there. The throw was just wide, he might have been struggling otherwise
bad line from Bresnan, and he's punished for it, glanced down to fine leg for four
slapped to the long-on boundary! Haddin steps away and Shahzad follows him, but it's full and invites a shot. A firm thump flies wide of mid-on and races over the rope
up and over extra cover this time! Shahzad went full, Haddin backed away and scooped the drive over the infield. The ball slows up on the outfield but has just enough on it to get over the line
to mid-off on the bounce this time! Haddin was lining up another big shot and but just went too early at this one, driving in the air but dropping short of mid-off, and they steal a single
nudged just wide of midwicket
Haddin plays from outside leg stump, but it's a defensive stroke back to the bowler
great fielding by Bell at extra cover! It was driven hard into the ground to his right, but he leapt across to cut the shot off cleanly
round the wicket he comes, landing the ball on middle and leg and Watson flicks out to deep midwicket
quick and aimed at middle stump, Haddin defends back to the bowler
Yardy slips towards leg stump but Haddin's shot goes straight to midwicket
Yardy continues to tuck him up quite nicely, no width to work with
nice and straight again, arrowed at middle and Haddin can only defend back to the bowler
and more defence to finish the over - a good one for Yardy and for England
a good length delivery, seaming in towards off stump, is defended back to the bowler
pushed down the leg side, the ball flicks the thigh pad and it takes a good, diving effort from Davies behind the stumps to cut that off
heaved across the line and out into the leg side, Trott runs across and hurls in the return, falling over as he does so, but can't prevent the two
inside edge, and the ball rolls just past the stumps! It was the slower ball from Bresnan
quicker and shorter, beating Watson for pace and striking him on the hip
chopped down to gully, and they take the chance for a quick single
tossed up on middle, a bit of inside edge and a bit of pad gets 'keeper and bowler interested, but there's no appeal
driven down to long-off, there's the 100. This is also, incidentally, Haddin and Watson's best opening stand for Australia
Haddin comes down the track and drives to long-off
slightly too wide, cut but straight to point
a toe-ended drive rolls into the covers
pushed just to the left of mid-on, there's a call for the run straight away and the sprint through
full on off stump, dug out towards mid-off

good shape away from the bat this time, that hasn't happened too often today. Possibly the legcutter once more, as the ball nips past the outside edge. As he has done all innings, Haddin had backed away to leg
fuller and straighter, defended to cover
a checked drive this time, again the ball goes to extra cover on the bounce
outside edge, genuine edge, and through the vacant slip region for four! Well wide of Davies, he had no chance
testing over from Shahzad, this time he fires in a yorker outside off and the ball nips right under the bat as Haddin jabs down at it. Through to the 'keeper
short from Swann, Watson was back and waiting for the aggressive pull but the ball just skidded through low to beat the bottom edge and land in Davies' gloves
Watson stays back again and punches wide of mid-off this time
just a bit too short, nice shot from Haddin, delicately late-cut down to third man. Yardy chases the ball down

slog sweep from Haddin, and he's picked out Shahzad at deep square leg! There's the breakthrough for England. The partnership is broken at 110, and Haddin departs for 39. It's not been the best knock from him, but he was doing a job and ticking along quite efficiently with Watson.
well forward to start, driving to cover
Clarke skips down, getting nicely to the pitch and driving down to long-off
a nervous, airy waft outside off from Clarke. The ball hit the seam and jagged away from him, beating the outside edge
tipped defensively towards point
now, is this ball starting to reverse? It certainly appears so, this one snakes in through the air as Clarke drives back down the track.
this one goes the other way, a sharp reversing outswinger! The ball takes the outside half of the bat and bounces behind point
slower ball this time, Watson steps well forward and defends square
sliced slightly by Watson, on the drive, but along the ground to extra cover
arm ball from Swann, it was much too short but Clarke couldn't do anything with it, his cut shot beaten on the top edge
down the pitch, and the ball is chipped just short of midwicket! Scratchy stuff from Clarke
he's down the track again, this time pushing back to the bowler
chopped down to gully, quick single taken
a flicked drive goes straight to midwicket
ah, that ruins what had been a really good over! Speared down the leg side, Davies can't do anything about that and that's four
Clarke is turned inside out by an outswinging, dipping low full-toss, popping it back to the bowler who fields in his follow through
just short of a good length, Clarke is back and defending
swinging out once again, the ball is full and wide and inviting the drive. Driven hard but straight to mid-off
definite swing for Shahzad, Clarke isn't quite sure which way it's going to go and is squared up as he pushes to mid-off
this one hoops in through the air, Clarke taps just wide of point and they sprint through
inswing again, but it comes out as a half-volley and Watson pushes to deep mid-off for one
drift through the air for Swann, and as the ball rushes through he beats the outside edge! There's an appeal from the bowler, but that hasn't hit anything
turning in from outside off, cut out to deep point
pulled across from outside off, down to long-on for one
full on off stump, flighted quite nicely and Watson drives back to the bowler
tossed up again by Swann, even slower this time, and again it goes back to the bowler
flicked to midwicket to end the over
loosener on leg stump to start, nudged to short fine leg for a scampered single, off the thigh
on a length and straight, Watson plays back when he might have been forward, but taps to mid-on safely enough
fired at leg stump, Watson misses an attempted glance but they take a leg bye off the pad
worked off the hip into the leg side
full and straight, driven down the ground for one
Clarke lines up a front foot pull, but a thick inside edge cannons off the pad and - luckily for him - rolls wide of the stumps
floated up temptingly on off stump, solid defence from the batsman

Australia needed a boundary to keep things under control, and Watson has provided it! Slog sweep from him, well in front of square, and out to straight midwicket. He cramps up after playing the shot, wincing in pain, which isn't a good sign
Swann pulls the length back a touch and is quicker through the air, defended
pushed out to long-off for one
Clarke dances out and takes the ball on the full, pushing down to long-on for one
a flat-footed swipe from Watson, it's chipped in the air towards long-off ...  but bounces just short of Tremlett! Watson is starting to look a bit weary here, and is targeting the boundary
glanced off the pad and out to deep square leg, they push hard for the second and Watson is strugging ... but he's back in time! The throw is also just wide, which helps
tapped down to gully
slower ball from Tremlett, or it's slightly slower through the air at any rate - the offcutter perhaps? Flicked straight to midwicket by Clarke
short, Clarke's weight is forward but he pulls nicely down to fine leg, a controlled shot
tapped down just to Morgan's left at point, they think about the single but the fielder is round in a flash and hurling in a shy at the stumps
bursting past the outside edge! That moved appreciably off the seam
pushed just behind square off the front foot
Watson is on the front foot, driving to cover
slightly too short, but skidding on and Watson can only nudge to midwicket
quicker one from Swann, pushed to the left of midwicket ... who slides but can't quite cut it off, a single is taken
driven rather more firmly down to long-on
flat on off stump, Watson stays back and punches back to the bowler
touch too short to start, forced out to deep cover
arrowed down flat on leg stump, Watson flicks but finds square leg
very quick through the air, really darted, but too wide down leg this time and Watson glances down to fine leg
heaved out to the straight midwicket boundary! Not the slog sweep, though he was down on one knee. Just swung across the line. Good connection
punched to cover for one

Clarke is forward, then back as he picks up the length, and nudging down to fine leg ... the throw comes back in very sharply as they come back for the second and is Clarke struggling here? They ask the third umpire to have a look! ... He's safe, but only just
whipped straight to man inside the circle at midwicket
tossed up outside off, Watson - on 94 - defends
leg-stump half-volley from Swann, and Watson brings up Australia's 150 with a glance to deep square
quicker through the air, off the pad and straight to short fine leg
Clarke jumps out and aims a wristy drive down to long-on
worked wide of the midwicket fielder, and the come back for an easy two
nudged to square leg, a diving fielder cuts it off but can't stop the single
Watson presents the full face of the bat and drives back to the bowler. He deserves a ton here
off the foot and rolling to Trott at short fine leg
quick and slightly short, Clarke hangs back and drives back to the bowler
eased down to long-off for one
driven straight to midwicket
he's full to start, and driven down to long-on
punched in the air down to long-on, another single taken
nudged just behind square on the leg side, a scrambled one

popped in the air! But just past Trott outstretched finger-tips, they sprint back for the second and there's the hundred for Watto! What a knock it's been, vital to his team's effort. Off comes the helmet, he's got a smile on his face and you can see how much that means
driven hard down to long-off
tip-and-run into the covers to end the over
Clarke uses his feet and takes the single down to long-on
power! Watson stands tall and absolutely hammers this, sending the ball arcing over Yardy's head and down to the straight boundary
and he follows that up with a quiet single to long-on, good batting
whipped to midwicket, straight to the fielder
very full, Clarke almost yorks himself as he steps out but gets some bat on it to send the ball to short fine leg
drilled very hard down to long-on, Watson looks like he's itching to step up a gear here
full, worked to midwicket
driven down to long-on, just the single
Clarke charges out of the crease but can't get to the pitch, defending
this time he stays back, working to midwicket
nicely driven down the ground, again just one run
a tired swipe across the line from Watson, he didn't get the greatest connection but still picks up a run
cracked past a diving extra cover, who gets a hand to it but can't stop the single. That sounded like a harder ball off the bat
huge! That is a really long boundary, and Watson has cleared it by some distance! It was a touch short and he just rocked back and clubbed it over midwicket
another! And this one's even bigger! This time he's on the front foot and slog-sweeping, getting right under it and lofting the ball deep into the crowd. Australia's fans are awake now!
he goes for it again, this one is miscued and swirls up into the Melbourne night! But falls safely! Watto can see the funny side
nudged to fine leg for one
single down to long-on
quick through the air, this newer ball has some bounce in it and it pops past the outside edge
looped up much, much slower this time. Clarke comes down the track and defends back to the bowler
yet another single from Clarke, down to long-on. What must his wagon-wheel look like...
swept hard by Watson, along the ground and scorching the turf down to long-leg ... but Shahzad is out there and fields cleanly
Clarke comes down the track, and drives well down the track but straight back to the bowler
a touch too short from Swann, Clarke backs away and cuts out to cover point
back of a length from Tremlett to start, Clarke hops back to defend

pulled down to Pietersen in the deep ... and what's going on out there? A few moments of utter chaos from England in the field. The original return throw ricocheted off the stumps, and they took an extra two ... and then Bresnan's throw went through Strauss's legs at cover and they took another! Four runs! Tremors isn't happy
back of a length again, defended to point
short, pulled in the air well in front of square on the leg side ... the ball plugs on the outfield though, just two
more length from Tremlett, defence from Clarke, and lots of noise from the crowd!
shaping away through the air, Clarke steps forward and drives out to the cover sweeper, they take on the fielder and that's good running, he's back safely for two
huge swipe from Watson, he misses completely and is lucky not to be bowled there! That skidded on, if it had turned he was a goner
top-edged just over Strauss at short fine leg! That popped off the glove and the England captain leapt up desperately but couldn't get a touch on it
more aggression from Watson, smiting a short one out to deep midwicket
slashed down behind square on the off side
powerful sweep from Watson, it's in the air for some distance but falls well short of Bresnan in the deep
that's gripped and turned! Popping up towards the hip, but negotiated by Clarke. And that ends Swann's contribution with the ball today
short to start, Watson attempts a paddle-pull but can't get it away, just the one
short again, pulled out to Pietersen and there's the 100 partnership
muscled out into the leg side
short yet again, pulled away and Trott charges round to keep them to one

chipped straight to cover! England strike, Clarke departs. Bresnan went full as Clarke stepped away to try and open up the off side, he drove well but in the air and Shahzad didn't have to move, just sticking his hands up to hold the catch.
dabbed down to short third man, Smith is desperate for the single but Watson sends him back just in time
crashed firmly down the ground, a superb exhibition of the on-drive ... but it's just one run with the fielder out there

slower-ball bouncer, a thick edge as Smith flails and the ball evades Davies! He threw everything at it, right off the toe of the bat and down to third man. Australia need more of the same - boundaries that is, not edges!
short and fast, pulled away off the front foot to midwicket, just one
back of a length, pulled in the air but dropping short of cow corner

a wild slash from Smith, a good, diving catch from Yardy at short third man! The ball was full and he tried to go over the off side in typical fashion, but a thick edge flew to Yardy, who tumbled to his left and held on well.
yorker from Shahzad, but flung down the leg side. Hussey loses his footing and falls over
tapped into space at cover, and they take the single
slower ball from Bresnan, misdirected down the leg side. Hussey glances and, on fresh legs, is back for the second in a flash!
half-volley on off stump, and classically driven by Hussey! Didn't try to over-hit it, just stepped forward and presented the face of the bat, bisecting mid-on and mid-off to collect four
short, pulled, the ball hangs in the air ... and that's landed right on the boundary marker! It was top-edged but there was pace on the ball and he went for it, Hussey is turning it on
chopped down on the off side, gully dives to save the run
worked off the hip, Hussey is like lightning between the stumps and is back for the second in quick time! How's Watto doing at the other end? He's blowing a bit...
pushed to wide mid-on, there's a chance for another two if they push hard ... but Watson's knackered and says no

huge, emotive appeal from Shahzad as Hussey is hit on the pad! But he's the only one to do so, and the umpire isn't interested. But they ask for the review. His foot is behind the line, so that's fine. No bat involved, it appears. But pitching just outside leg, so the decision stands. That was mighty close though!
cracked very hard into the covers, but that's a great stop by the fielder
landing on leg stump, Hussey flicks down to fine leg
Shahzad goes full again, has this just come off the pad? They take a run, yep it's a leg bye
slower ball, tapped down to gully
another slower ball, pushed towards mid-off and they scamper through
full toss, slapped back to the bowler who fields in his follow through and hurls a shy at the stumps to send Hussey scampering back to his crease
whipped well off the toes and out to deep midwicket, just the two runs as a tired Watson sweats the second

slower ball, chipped in the air and Tremlett takes the catch at square leg! The match turns again, this could change everything. A quick innings from Hussey but Australia still want 51 and there could be a few jitters in the dressing room now
back of a length to start, tapped down to gully
this time he does get the single, down to third man

Bresnan aims for the yorker, but sprays it down the leg side and the umpire signals wide. The bowler isn't happy, he thinks that clipped the pad. Watto is limping though, suggesting he's hit his own ankle with the bat
sharp yorker, and Watson is knocked off his feet! That was quick and right at his toes, Watson jammed down and slipped over as he did so
driven on the up to Bell at cover
crunched down to long-off, Watson back on strike
fired full and fast at off stump. Medium pace, rather than spin!
full again, Watson looks for the big shot but can only get one down to long-on. That is, however, his career-best score in ODIs
flayed into the covers, Bell gets his hands to it to take the power out of the shot, good effort
glanced to short fine leg, straight to the fielder and no run!
short, White doesn't pick it up and is struck in the midriff as he shapes to pull. That smarts a bit...
pressure! It's building now, White is struck on the pad as he's beaten by a bit of pace and bounce and is struck on the pad. The ball goes to point, no run
smeared across the line, down to long-on. There's the 250
it is full, just outside off, driven hard into the ground and the ball bounces up and over Tremlett (no mean feat) and down to long-off
back of a length again, White swings hard but again it's just one to long-on.
full, swinging, but the line is wrong and there's the boundary Australia needed! Flicked down to fine leg, the ball beats the fielder at short fine
short, slower-ball bouncer and White pulls out to deep square
full, lifted off the pads and bouncing out to deep midwicket. Shahzad charges round and fires in the return
full, close to the yorker but he jams down hard on it and gets the ball down to long-on
back of a length, White tries to run it down to third man but can't beat the fielder in close.
slower ball, really quite short and White pulls out into the deep ... they charge back for the second!
wide! Short again from Bresnan, the quick one this time but ballooning over the batsman and down the leg side

no surprises, short again and pulled out into the deep ... and actually Bresnan's been no-balled for this bouncer! It won't be a Free Hit - his front foot was fine - but Bresnan's not happy. He says he wasn't told one for the over
full, straight, clipped and two runs! Good over for Australia
short, rising on White and he hooks ... the top edge goes miles up, Trott charges in and falls forward, he gets both hands to it but the ball bobbles out!
short again, hoicked wildly out to wide long-on, and that's four
the plan may just be misfiring now, White knows it's going to be short every ball and is waiting for it, pulling out to deep square leg
full, swiped powerfully out to deep midwicket and there's 150 for Watto! His arms are aloft, the crowd cheer their approval and Australia are closing in on the win now
again Watson targets midwicket with the lofted shot, this time he doesn't get the best connection but the ball falls short of the fielder out there
short yet again, outside off but White hooks across into the leg side
full, fast and swinging. The ball takes the inside half of the bat and rolls out on the leg side, and they're back for the second run
White lays bat on ball, tapping towards mid-off and setting off straight away for a scampered single
short, Watson ducks underneath it ... and that's one for the over
pinpoint yorker from Shahzad, and Watson can only dig it out back to the bowler.
full toss, Watson whips into the leg side but hits Strauss at midwicket
slower ball, full outside off and Watson swings it into the leg side ... it won't be the boundary though, Pietersen sprints across to cut it off
full, right in the blockhole. White slams down on it but mid-on charges round
the attempted yorker slips out as a low full toss, and White lifts it to the wide long-on boundary! Is that the blow that puts Australia definitively ahead?
another great yorker, White digs it out to cover
another full toss, this time White can't capitalise and picks up just one out to deep square
perfect yorker from Bresnan, you simply can't put that away and Watson digs it out to midwicket
very full, Watson meets it on the full and powers the ball down to long-on
Watson roars Australia's victory! What a way to do it, a full toss is cracked baseball-style into the crowd behind long-on!
